<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the best AI tool for B2B sales prospecting?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Perplexity Pro is the best tool specifically for B2B sales prospecting research because it surfaces recent funding news, leadership changes, and company events with verifiable citations. Use it for the research phase, then bring those findings into Claude to draft personalized outreach. The combination outperforms either tool alone."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Claude or ChatGPT better for B2B sales teams?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Claude is better for B2B sales teams that need shared workflows. Claude's Projects feature lets your whole team operate against the same ICP, voice guidelines, and battle cards, so every rep gets consistent outputs without re-explaining context. ChatGPT is a closer call if your team also wants access to the broader GPT marketplace."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does a full AI sales stack cost per year?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"A complete AI sales stack for a 10-person B2B team typically runs $5,000 to $10,000 per year. That covers a general-purpose AI like Claude Team ($30/seat/mo), Perplexity Pro for research leads ($20/mo), a call recording tool like Fathom (free to $20/seat) or Gong ($1,200 to $1,600/seat/year for enterprise), plus your existing CRM and engagement platform."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do AI SDR tools that send automated outreach actually work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. Fully automated AI SDR tools that send cold outreach without human review have not delivered the promised results. Reply rates are poor, the messaging is generic, and the brand damage from bad outreach outweighs any volume advantage. The better approach is using AI like Claude to help human reps write faster, not to replace the rep entirely."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What AI tools does Gong use and how does it compare to Fathom?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Gong uses its own proprietary AI models for call transcription, deal risk scoring, and coaching recommendations. Fathom uses AI for transcription and meeting summaries as well. The key difference is scale and depth: Gong is built for 10+ rep enterprise teams with deep CRM analytics, while Fathom is better for 1 to 5 person teams that need clean summaries without the enterprise price tag ($20/seat versus $1,200 to $1,600/seat/year)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I use Claude inside HubSpot or Salesforce for sales?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Not natively inside the CRM interface, but in practice most teams copy-paste or use Claude via API in their workflows. Claude handles account briefs, email personalization, and follow-up drafts outside the CRM, then reps paste the output in. Some teams use Zapier or Make to connect Claude outputs directly into HubSpot records. HubSpot's own AI and Salesforce Einstein are built-in options but are generally less capable than Claude for freeform writing tasks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What AI tools should a small B2B sales team of 1 to 5 people start with?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Start with two tools: Claude Pro ($20/mo) for writing, research, and workflow automation, and Fathom (free tier available) for call recording and meeting summaries. Those two cover 80 percent of where AI delivers measurable value for small sales teams. Add Perplexity Pro ($20/mo) once prospecting research becomes a regular bottleneck. Avoid buying specialized point solutions until you have consistently high usage of those core two."}}]}</script>
