<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Roundup &middot; 2026</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">Best AI tools <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">for B2B sales.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      An opinionated breakdown of the AI tools actually worth a B2B sales team's budget in 2026. By category. With specific picks and the ones to skip. No affiliate deals. No paid placement. The recommendations reflect what we actually deploy with clients.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">The premise</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Most "best AI for sales" lists are useless</h2>
    <p class="body">A typical roundup includes 30 tools, hedges on every recommendation, and conveniently happens to list the ones the writer has affiliate links for. The result: B2B sales leaders are paying for 6 AI tools, using 2, and wondering why their team's output hasn't changed.</p>
    <p class="body">This list is different. Categories of work. One clear pick per category. The runner-up if you want it. And explicit lists of what to skip and why.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Quick comparison</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Top AI tools for B2B sales: pricing and fit at a glance</h2>
    <p class="body">The table below covers the tools that consistently make the final stack for B2B sales teams. Use it to get oriented, then read the category breakdowns below for the reasoning.</p>
    <div style="overflow-x:auto;">
      <table class="compare-table">
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>Tool</th>
            <th>Category</th>
            <th>Starting price</th>
            <th>Best for</th>
            <th>Skip if...</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Claude Team <span class="tag-best">Top pick</span></td>
            <td>General-purpose AI</td>
            <td>$30/seat/mo</td>
            <td>Shared sales workflows: account briefs, email drafts, battle cards, proposals</td>
            <td>Your team won't adopt a shared Projects workflow</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>ChatGPT Team</td>
            <td>General-purpose AI</td>
            <td>$30/seat/mo</td>
            <td>Teams that also want GPT marketplace plugins and code interpreter</td>
            <td>You primarily need consistent long-form writing quality</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Perplexity Pro <span class="tag-best">Top pick</span></td>
            <td>Cited research</td>
            <td>$20/mo individual</td>
            <td>Prospect research: funding news, leadership changes, recent press</td>
            <td>Your reps don't do significant research before outreach</td>
          </tr>
